WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:25.025 --> 00:26.890
Thank you.

00:26.926 --> 00:28.860
Well, I'd like to thank
our own Mr. Pruit

00:28.895 --> 00:30.692
for an incredible
unplugged evening.

00:30.730 --> 00:32.925
It's his last here
before heading off

00:32.966 --> 00:35.161
to cut his own very first album.

00:35.201 --> 00:38.102
So, uh, from all of us, Ray...

00:38.138 --> 00:39.901
don't forget us
and good luck, okay?

00:39.939 --> 00:41.406
Thanks. I won't.

00:46.880 --> 00:49.371
Did you tell Kelly yet
about the weekend?

00:50.950 --> 00:53.111
Not yet.

00:53.153 --> 00:55.212
What, what? We're still
driving up, aren't we?

00:55.255 --> 00:57.155
Yeah, yeah, I got my dad

00:57.190 --> 00:59.021
to lend us his station wagon
for the drive.

00:59.059 --> 01:00.924
Oh, cool, how long
of a trip is it?

01:00.960 --> 01:01.949
It's, like, five hours.

01:02.028 --> 01:03.461
But the spa will be worth it.

01:03.496 --> 01:06.556
The brochure offers
a stress-free slice of heaven.

01:06.599 --> 01:08.863
Uh, I don't exactly know

01:08.902 --> 01:12.668
if it'll be stress-free,
but... it'll be fun.

01:12.705 --> 01:14.639
Why won't it be stress-free?

01:14.674 --> 01:17.768
Well, my advice is
tell your parents

01:17.811 --> 01:20.405
you need a lot more money
and then let Jim whittle you...

01:20.447 --> 01:22.506
Nat, I made a house budget.

01:22.549 --> 01:23.516
I went over it.

01:23.550 --> 01:24.778
I have to deal with it.

01:24.818 --> 01:26.217
Hey, Bran,

01:26.252 --> 01:29.483
come on over here,
I want you to meet somebody.

01:29.522 --> 01:31.490
Brandon Walsh.
Johnnie Mars.

01:31.524 --> 01:33.082
Location scout extraordinaire.

01:33.126 --> 01:34.991
Nice to meet you. Steve's been
talking about you all week.

01:35.095 --> 01:36.426
Well, same here.

01:36.463 --> 01:38.090
Hey, loved your house.

01:38.131 --> 01:40.156
It's exactly what the
director's looking for.

01:40.200 --> 01:41.792
- It's perfect for the film.
- Great.

01:41.835 --> 01:43.393
He wants to book
your house today.

01:43.436 --> 01:44.733
$1,200 a day.

01:44.771 --> 01:45.999
What do I have to do?

01:46.039 --> 01:47.199
Just sign right here.

01:49.509 --> 01:52.000
How could you have
invited Valerie?

01:52.078 --> 01:53.807
I'm stressed out
just thinking about it.

01:53.847 --> 01:54.905
What was I gonna do?

01:54.948 --> 01:55.972
She found out
we were going.

01:56.015 --> 01:57.277
- What could I say?
- How about "no."

01:57.317 --> 01:58.648
I mean, just because she exists,

01:58.685 --> 02:00.380
doesn't mean
she has to be included.

02:00.420 --> 02:02.445
I know, I know, but Donna
wanted her to come, too,

02:02.489 --> 02:04.480
so, I don't know,
I just thought it would be okay.

02:04.524 --> 02:06.424
- Is that so?
- Kel, it won't be

02:06.459 --> 02:08.120
that bad, I promise, okay?

02:08.161 --> 02:10.253
Besides, do you really
want to leave Valerie

02:10.295 --> 02:11.456
alone in town with Colin?

02:11.498 --> 02:13.659
I would've taken my
chances, thank you.

02:15.368 --> 02:16.426
Too late.

02:16.469 --> 02:17.629
Hey.

02:17.670 --> 02:19.228
So that road trip
we're going on

02:19.272 --> 02:20.330
sounds like fun,
huh, Kel?

02:20.373 --> 02:22.898
Hmm?

03:40.587 --> 03:41.918
Hi.

03:41.955 --> 03:43.980
Is it a bad time?

03:44.090 --> 03:46.786
No, I was just packing up.

03:46.826 --> 03:48.623
The girls will be here
any minute.

03:51.864 --> 03:54.662
I, uh, I just wanted
to return your notes.

03:54.701 --> 03:56.259
They helped me a lot.
Thanks.

03:56.302 --> 03:58.167
Well, I knew you
could catch up.

03:58.204 --> 04:01.731
Hey, listen, uh,
jean jacket or parka?

04:01.774 --> 04:02.798
Probably both.

04:02.842 --> 04:04.469
It gets kind of
cold there at night.

04:06.646 --> 04:08.375
You know, I have to admit

04:08.414 --> 04:10.109
I'm really looking
forward to this.

04:10.149 --> 04:13.915
I'm actually kind of surprised
you got invited.

04:13.953 --> 04:17.149
Well, I kind of invited myself.

04:17.190 --> 04:18.918
Getting out of town

04:18.958 --> 04:22.291
may give Kelly and me
a chance to mend some fences.

04:23.930 --> 04:24.954
Look,

04:24.998 --> 04:27.330
Val...

04:29.936 --> 04:35.568
you helped me through some real
dark hours last week and, uh...

04:35.608 --> 04:38.338
I just want you to know that
I, I really appreciate it.

04:38.378 --> 04:39.936
Thanks.

04:39.979 --> 04:44.439
Well, you don't have
to thank me.

04:44.484 --> 04:46.952
You know, I've been
thinking about you, too.

04:48.421 --> 04:50.753
And, David...

05:01.134 --> 05:03.034
Have a good time.

05:03.069 --> 05:05.060
See you when you get back.

05:55.988 --> 05:58.422
Dylan.

05:58.458 --> 06:00.619
Good, you remember
my name.

06:00.660 --> 06:02.685
And you still remember
where to find me

06:02.729 --> 06:04.390
on Friday mornings.

06:10.103 --> 06:11.400
Yes, I sure do.

06:14.774 --> 06:16.264
What's this?

06:16.309 --> 06:18.937
It's just...

06:19.011 --> 06:21.036
it's my way of apologizing.

06:21.080 --> 06:23.947
You've been giving me the
brush-off for a couple of days,

06:24.016 --> 06:25.950
so I know I did something.

06:26.018 --> 06:27.417
Yeah, you did.

06:29.389 --> 06:33.086
Well, what is it?

06:33.126 --> 06:34.684
I mean...

06:34.727 --> 06:37.127
give it to me straight;
I can take it.

06:37.163 --> 06:38.562
Okay.

06:38.598 --> 06:41.192
The other night
at my dinner party...

06:41.234 --> 06:43.293
why were you snooping
in my father's study?

06:43.336 --> 06:44.928
- That's what this is about?
- Mm.

06:44.971 --> 06:47.439
Well, it was just curiosity.

06:47.473 --> 06:49.566
- I mean, it got
the better of me. - Look...

06:49.609 --> 06:52.134
if you respect me,
you'll respect my father,

06:52.178 --> 06:54.510
our home and our privacy.

06:54.547 --> 06:56.139
Dylan, that's important to me.

06:56.182 --> 06:58.810
Well, if it's important to you,
it's important to me, too.

07:02.755 --> 07:05.121
How did you know
that I like teddy bears?

07:05.158 --> 07:07.786
Oh, it was easy... I was
snooping in your closet.

07:13.499 --> 07:14.761
Will you pass the pretzels?

07:14.801 --> 07:15.859
Oh, yeah.

07:15.902 --> 07:18.132
Okay, let's get
back to the game.

07:18.171 --> 07:19.934
New category.

07:20.039 --> 07:21.802
Best pretzels.

07:21.841 --> 07:23.638
Saltless.

07:23.676 --> 07:24.734
Regular.

07:24.777 --> 07:26.404
With mustard and cheese.

07:26.446 --> 07:27.811
All of the above.

07:27.847 --> 07:29.712
Pass 'em back up here.

07:29.749 --> 07:31.148
Thank you.
Okay...

07:31.184 --> 07:32.549
Best beach.

07:32.585 --> 07:34.951
Mm... Station eight,
Santa Monica.

07:35.021 --> 07:36.682
No, too many
high schoolers.

07:36.722 --> 07:38.815
Paradise Cove
after Labor Day.

07:38.858 --> 07:40.621
Oh, that is the best beach.

07:40.660 --> 07:42.287
I had my best kiss there.

07:42.328 --> 07:43.295
Ooh, I like.

07:43.329 --> 07:44.728
Who with?

07:44.764 --> 07:46.698
Oh, we're not up
to that category yet.

07:48.334 --> 07:50.131
Clare, where are you going?

07:50.169 --> 07:51.761
I'm just gonna take
a little shortcut.

07:51.804 --> 07:53.135
Are you sure you know
where you're going?

07:53.172 --> 07:54.264
Yeah, David and I

07:54.307 --> 07:55.774
took this road last year
when we came up here

07:55.808 --> 07:58.402
looking for UFO's, remember?

07:58.444 --> 08:00.605
Wait.

08:00.646 --> 08:02.511
On my map,
it's just a dotted line.

08:02.548 --> 08:04.015
Yeah, but just for,
like, ten miles.

08:04.050 --> 08:06.018
Back to my
favorite category.

08:06.052 --> 08:07.451
Best kiss...
Kel, who with?

08:07.487 --> 08:08.749
Not gonna tell you.

08:08.788 --> 08:10.722
I know who it was.
Who?

08:10.756 --> 08:13.350
That girl, Alison.

08:13.392 --> 08:15.292
Oh, it was not!

08:15.328 --> 08:16.352
Then tell.

08:16.395 --> 08:17.794
Come on, no secrets
on this trip.

08:17.830 --> 08:19.263
That's right, no secrets.

08:19.298 --> 08:20.925
All right, fine.
It was Dylan.

08:21.000 --> 08:22.126
Really?

08:22.168 --> 08:23.260
Not Brandon or Colin?

08:23.302 --> 08:26.601
Well, Brandon wins
for consistency,

08:26.639 --> 08:29.199
and Colin wins
for intensity, but...

08:29.242 --> 08:31.802
nothing will beat that night
on the beach with Dylan.

08:31.844 --> 08:34.745
Okay, who's next?

08:34.780 --> 08:35.940
Best kiss.

08:36.015 --> 08:37.505
Um, for me, David.

08:37.549 --> 08:39.073
Yeah, me, too.
David Silver.

08:39.118 --> 08:40.278
What about you, Valerie?

08:40.318 --> 08:42.082
Was it Brandon,

08:42.121 --> 08:45.147
Dylan, Steve, Colin, um...

08:49.929 --> 08:53.092
David.

08:53.132 --> 08:54.292
You kissed David?

08:54.333 --> 08:55.732
Just once.

08:55.768 --> 08:56.962
When?

08:57.036 --> 08:58.333
This morning.

08:58.371 --> 08:59.395
Well, don't stop now.

08:59.438 --> 09:00.928
Come on,
let's hear it.

09:00.973 --> 09:02.668
I don't think
I want to hear any more.

09:02.708 --> 09:03.732
Next category.

09:03.776 --> 09:05.676
Um...

09:05.711 --> 09:08.271
favorite cartoon
characters?

09:12.919 --> 09:14.910
Thanks for fixing
the chandelier, Ray.

09:14.954 --> 09:16.615
I want everything shipshape
for the movie crew.

09:16.656 --> 09:18.920
Whether they need it or not,
we'll be ready for 'em.

09:18.991 --> 09:21.323
All right,
stereo system's all set.

09:21.360 --> 09:22.691
Quad speakers, the works.

09:22.728 --> 09:23.922
Yes. Thanks, Silver.

09:24.030 --> 09:26.521
So are we going to get
to meet any stars or what?

09:26.566 --> 09:28.534
Uh... I don't think so.

09:30.703 --> 09:33.171
Look, I'll level with you guys.

09:33.205 --> 09:35.799
They're making a...

09:35.841 --> 09:38.833
an art film, you know?

09:38.878 --> 09:39.867
No, not exactly.

09:39.912 --> 09:40.936
What's an art film?

09:41.047 --> 09:43.277
Take a wild, wild...

09:43.316 --> 09:45.250
wild guess.

09:46.352 --> 09:47.546
I give up.

09:47.587 --> 09:48.611
Don't disappoint me, Silver.

09:48.654 --> 09:51.054
They're shooting
a skin flick here?

09:51.090 --> 09:52.421
Not a skin flick.

09:52.458 --> 09:56.224
Cinematic software for the adult
entertainment industry.

09:56.262 --> 09:57.524
- Oh, a porno.
- For real?

09:57.563 --> 09:58.587
They're gonna shoot it here?

09:59.699 --> 10:01.098
And Brandon okayed this?

10:01.133 --> 10:03.124
Well, I haven't exactly
gotten around

10:03.169 --> 10:04.864
to telling him
about that part yet.

10:06.138 --> 10:07.867
He'll be fine.

10:07.907 --> 10:10.569
Steve says they're going to be
filming at the house till late,

10:10.610 --> 10:12.669
so I figure we should
go have an early meal

10:12.712 --> 10:13.906
and then go over and watch.

10:13.946 --> 10:14.970
What do you say?

10:15.081 --> 10:17.242
Thanks, but no thanks.

10:17.283 --> 10:18.511
You're not working tonight.

10:18.551 --> 10:19.984
Why don't you
come over and hang?

10:20.052 --> 10:21.849
Didn't I just
politely decline?

10:21.887 --> 10:24.151
Which word was unclear?

10:24.190 --> 10:26.351
We could be extras?

10:26.392 --> 10:28.326
Been there, done that,
bought the T-shirt.

10:28.361 --> 10:30.295
That's right, I forgot.

10:30.329 --> 10:33.457
Miss Sophisticated
has seen everything.

10:33.499 --> 10:35.126
Except my house.

10:35.167 --> 10:36.930
What's so special
about your house, anyway?

10:36.969 --> 10:38.368
Nothing special about my house.

10:38.404 --> 10:40.599
It's just a Spanish split-
level in Beverly Hills,

10:40.640 --> 10:42.631
but you know,
I just want you to be

10:42.675 --> 10:44.438
part of my life,
is that so wrong?

10:44.477 --> 10:46.707
Look, I'm just
a little embarrassed

10:46.746 --> 10:48.907
to tell you what I'm really
doing tonight, that's all.

10:48.948 --> 10:51.382
You know, I have a sister.

10:51.417 --> 10:54.113
If this is a feminine hygiene
problem, I can handle it.

10:54.153 --> 10:56.348
I may even be able to help
you out a little bit with it.

10:56.389 --> 10:59.222
Hardly.

10:59.258 --> 11:00.850
I'm fourth in a bridge game

11:00.893 --> 11:02.155
at my great-aunt's house
in Toluca Lake,

11:02.194 --> 11:03.627
and I can't get out of it, okay?

11:03.663 --> 11:04.925
Family obligations.

11:04.964 --> 11:06.363
Why didn't you just say
so in the first place?

11:06.399 --> 11:10.062
Because it's so... uncool.

11:10.102 --> 11:12.366
Yeah, it's uncool, but
it's kinda cute, too.

11:12.405 --> 11:14.669
Don't worry, I won't
tell anybody, I swear.

11:14.707 --> 11:16.140
Thanks.

11:16.175 --> 11:17.369
You're welcome.

11:21.180 --> 11:22.977
See you tomorrow.
Okay.

11:28.821 --> 11:31.153
Clare, where are we?

11:31.190 --> 11:32.418
Relax. We're right
where we should be.

11:32.458 --> 11:34.449
Okay, I've got one.

11:34.493 --> 11:36.188
No holds barred.

11:36.228 --> 11:37.695
Best song to make out to.

11:37.730 --> 11:38.924
Anything by Barry White.

11:38.964 --> 11:40.556
Barry White?!

11:40.599 --> 11:42.294
He's, like, old.

11:42.334 --> 11:43.631
He's, like, fat.

11:43.669 --> 11:44.931
He's, like, cool.

11:44.970 --> 11:46.665
Everybody in New York
is listening to him.

11:46.706 --> 11:47.866
That voice.

11:47.907 --> 11:51.365
Oh, so you and Colin
do it to Barry, huh?

11:51.410 --> 11:54.675
No. Colin's so retro.

11:54.714 --> 11:57.615
He likes to make out to Mozart.

11:57.650 --> 11:59.379
What about you, Donna?

11:59.418 --> 12:00.783
You've been awfully quiet.

12:00.820 --> 12:02.913
Well, maybe I just don't
like to talk about sex

12:02.955 --> 12:04.582
as much as you guys do.

12:04.623 --> 12:06.955
You know, that's all we've
talked about since we left L.A.

12:07.059 --> 12:08.686
You even rated
cartoon characters

12:08.728 --> 12:09.820
on which one was sexiest.

12:09.862 --> 12:11.693
I still say Woody Woodpecker.

12:11.731 --> 12:13.255
Have you been with him?

12:13.299 --> 12:15.961
You've been with everybody else.

12:16.068 --> 12:18.161
And what's that
supposed to mean?

12:18.204 --> 12:19.933
It's true, Val.

12:19.972 --> 12:21.769
This has been
quite a year for you.

12:21.807 --> 12:23.570
I don't know if you have
enough wall space

12:23.609 --> 12:25.577
in your bedroom for all the
trophy heads, do you?

12:25.611 --> 12:26.976
You know what you guys?

12:27.046 --> 12:28.536
I'm sick of this.

12:28.581 --> 12:29.946
You love to talk behind my back.

12:29.982 --> 12:32.280
Why don't we just get things
out in the open, huh?

12:32.318 --> 12:33.444
I'd be glad to.

12:33.486 --> 12:34.384
You know what, Donna,
come off it.

12:34.420 --> 12:35.853
I mean, Clare goes out

12:35.888 --> 12:38.118
with David for a few months
and you don't say a damn thing.

12:38.157 --> 12:39.954
I kiss him one time
and you sit in the back seat

12:39.992 --> 12:41.983
and sulk for the last
half an hour.

12:42.061 --> 12:44.154
Yeah, well, David's not the one
I've been thinking about.

12:44.196 --> 12:45.720
Come on, once and for all,

12:45.765 --> 12:47.995
what really happened
between you and Ray?

12:48.100 --> 12:50.728
Okay, let's change
the subject.

12:50.770 --> 12:52.135
Favorite Russian novels...
Kel? Anyone?

12:52.171 --> 12:54.731
No, no, no...
no secrets here, Valerie.

12:54.774 --> 12:55.934
All right.

12:58.144 --> 12:59.236
I slept with him.

13:01.013 --> 13:02.275
Twice.

13:02.314 --> 13:03.781
Oh, my God.

13:03.816 --> 13:05.408
I think I'm going to be sick.

13:05.451 --> 13:07.442
You really are a slut,
aren't you?

13:07.486 --> 13:08.453
Oh, please.

13:08.487 --> 13:09.681
Don't act so surprised.

13:09.722 --> 13:11.087
Like Clare didn't

13:11.123 --> 13:12.420
tell you months ago.

13:12.458 --> 13:14.187
Clare, you knew about this,
and you didn't tell me?

13:14.226 --> 13:16.956
If you knew something like
that about my boyfriend,

13:17.062 --> 13:19.496
- would you have told me?
- No, but you could have told me.

13:19.532 --> 13:21.932
Well, I thought David
told you, you know,

13:21.967 --> 13:23.525
David knew about this, too?

13:23.569 --> 13:24.763
Stop the car.

13:24.804 --> 13:26.669
I'm gonna throw up.

13:36.782 --> 13:39.410
I hope you're proud
of yourself.

13:55.267 --> 13:56.666
I just want to go home.

13:56.702 --> 13:57.828
Come on, you'll be fine.

13:57.870 --> 13:59.098
How can I be fine?

13:59.138 --> 14:01.333
Ray cheated on me
and lied to me for months.

14:01.373 --> 14:03.603
Well, I think maybe
the weekend will do you good.

14:03.642 --> 14:05.872
You know what, you don't even
have to talk to Valerie.

14:05.911 --> 14:08.675
Yeah, as an added bonus,
none of us do.

14:08.714 --> 14:09.874
I heard that.

14:09.915 --> 14:11.143
Good.

14:11.183 --> 14:12.775
What do you guys want me to do?

14:12.818 --> 14:14.308
Just run alongside the car?

14:14.353 --> 14:16.378
You know what, I think
we'd all feel a lot better

14:16.422 --> 14:17.650
if a hole opened
up beneath you

14:17.690 --> 14:18.679
and you just
disappeared forever.

14:18.724 --> 14:20.385
Very funny.

14:20.426 --> 14:22.656
You guys, come on,
let's go.

14:22.695 --> 14:24.492
Yeah, before anything
else happens.

14:31.503 --> 14:33.971
Houston, we have a problem.

14:34.073 --> 14:36.541
Well, that's one thing
you can't blame on me.

14:36.575 --> 14:38.304
Oh yes, we can.
You were sitting in the car.

14:38.344 --> 14:40.539
What's the matter with it?

14:40.579 --> 14:41.568
You guys relax, all right?

14:41.614 --> 14:43.206
I just need to get
under the hood.

14:43.249 --> 14:45.945
Oh, that'll be a big help.

14:45.985 --> 14:48.146
I took auto mechanics
in summer school once.

14:48.187 --> 14:49.779
Excuse me.

14:49.822 --> 14:51.187
Maybe when I look

14:51.223 --> 14:53.487
at the engine,
it'll come back to me.

14:59.632 --> 15:00.599
Well?

15:00.633 --> 15:02.567
It's not coming back to me.

15:06.405 --> 15:09.169
Can I be of assistance?

15:10.276 --> 15:11.504
Oh, yes, Sister,

15:11.543 --> 15:12.908
you can definitely help.

15:12.945 --> 15:14.173
You're a godsend.

15:18.951 --> 15:21.943
This room will be perfect
for your party scene.

15:22.021 --> 15:25.081
But of course.

15:25.124 --> 15:27.217
Hey, you need any extras
for tonight?

15:29.461 --> 15:30.951
What is your name?

15:31.030 --> 15:32.497
Me, I'm Steve.

15:32.531 --> 15:33.498
Steve.

15:33.532 --> 15:34.521
Sit.

15:34.566 --> 15:37.694
Is this an audition?

