29:51.790 --> 29:54.691
- He asked that you start
without him. - Thank you.

29:55.727 --> 29:58.059
Well, this isn't like him.

30:12.577 --> 30:14.602
All right!

30:14.646 --> 30:17.410
Explain yourself quickly,
then go home.

30:17.448 --> 30:18.938
Can I come in?

30:18.983 --> 30:20.541
Not without delousing.

30:20.585 --> 30:23.816
Pornography is something
I find particularly revolting.

30:23.855 --> 30:26.949
Susan, I was as surprised as you
were about what was going on.

30:26.991 --> 30:29.391
My roommate has the occasional
lapse in good judgment.

30:29.427 --> 30:31.122
Well, if it is true
that we are known

30:31.162 --> 30:33.926
by the company that we keep,
then what does it say about you

30:33.965 --> 30:35.865
that you are living
with some kind of pervert?

30:35.900 --> 30:38.596
Not to mention, one that
is so clueless he cheated

30:38.636 --> 30:40.263
on a placement test.

30:40.305 --> 30:42.330
How do you know about that?

30:42.373 --> 30:44.398
- That's confidential.
- Please.

30:44.442 --> 30:47.002
The story is legendary
among the math faculty.

30:47.045 --> 30:48.273
Steve's a bonehead.

30:48.313 --> 30:51.476
No, Steve's actions
were bonehead.

30:51.516 --> 30:52.949
But 20 years down the road,

30:52.984 --> 30:54.884
Steve's still gonna be
my best friend.

30:54.919 --> 30:58.082
I can't say the same for
the next 20 seconds with you.

30:59.691 --> 31:02.489
Wait a minute.

31:03.962 --> 31:06.658
You swear you didn't know
anything about this?

31:06.698 --> 31:09.223
No. I'm saying
I didn't know what it was

31:09.267 --> 31:10.598
until I got there tonight.

31:10.635 --> 31:14.196
And maybe I should have
stopped it sooner, but...

31:14.239 --> 31:15.900
I didn't.

31:20.845 --> 31:22.176
Come in.

31:38.630 --> 31:42.430
Who am I to blame Valerie
for sleeping around?

31:42.467 --> 31:46.426
Let she who has not sinned
cast the first stone.

31:46.471 --> 31:48.496
I've sinned as much as anybody.

31:48.539 --> 31:51.406
I slept with
my best friend's boyfriend.

31:51.442 --> 31:54.673
I slept with
my boyfriend's best friend.

31:54.712 --> 31:57.840
I hope at least God
can forgive me.

32:00.752 --> 32:03.220
Listen, God,
if you're up there,

32:03.254 --> 32:05.119
I don't ask for a lot.

32:05.156 --> 32:07.454
I just need friends,
like everybody else.

32:07.492 --> 32:09.824
And I always seem
to screw 'em up.

32:09.861 --> 32:11.556
Maybe you could help me out.

32:11.596 --> 32:14.497
And while you're at it,
could you look out for Donna?

32:14.532 --> 32:16.227
Your sweetest lamb
hasn't figured out,

32:16.267 --> 32:18.360
when her boyfriend
throws her down the stairs,

32:18.403 --> 32:20.667
it doesn't mean "I love you."

32:22.373 --> 32:24.466
Now I lay me down to sleep,

32:24.509 --> 32:26.568
I pray the Lord my soul to keep.

32:26.611 --> 32:28.738
If I should die before I wake,

32:28.780 --> 32:31.578
I pray the Lord my soul to take.

32:31.616 --> 32:34.744
God bless
my family and friends,

32:34.786 --> 32:36.413
even Valerie,

32:36.454 --> 32:37.648
the witch!

32:37.689 --> 32:39.680
Amen.

32:41.859 --> 32:44.327
Uh... listen, God,

32:44.362 --> 32:46.523
I just want to know one thing.

32:46.564 --> 32:48.964
When Sartre wrote No Exit,

32:49.000 --> 32:51.696
was he thinking of this place?

32:58.409 --> 33:00.809
Mmm. I never got
what the attraction

33:00.845 --> 33:02.335
of pornography was, anyway.

33:02.380 --> 33:04.041
Some people think it's erotic.

33:04.082 --> 33:05.947
If you knew how many
convicted rapists

33:05.984 --> 33:07.281
are regular porn watchers,

33:07.318 --> 33:09.912
you may not be
such a fan, either.

33:09.954 --> 33:12.616
I can't believe I'm hearing
a censorship argument

33:12.657 --> 33:14.318
from a newspaper woman.

33:14.359 --> 33:15.951
I wouldn't ban it.

33:16.027 --> 33:19.360
But I wouldn't invite it
into my living room, either.

33:19.397 --> 33:21.661
Ah.

33:21.699 --> 33:24.930
I'm never gonna live
this one down, am I?

33:24.969 --> 33:26.197
No.

33:26.237 --> 33:28.228
Didn't think so.

33:29.807 --> 33:32.241
So, what do you find erotic?

33:32.276 --> 33:34.836
Well... the massage
was a good start.

33:34.879 --> 33:35.971
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

33:36.047 --> 33:38.481
What else?

33:38.516 --> 33:40.507
Hot baths...

33:40.551 --> 33:42.212
candles...

33:42.253 --> 33:44.312
You know, romance.

33:44.355 --> 33:45.982
- Romance is good.
- Mm-hmm.

33:46.024 --> 33:47.855
Except you'd probably
want to videotape it.

33:47.892 --> 33:50.053
Never on the first date.

33:51.462 --> 33:53.760
I'm glad you stayed.

33:53.798 --> 33:56.528
So am I.

33:56.567 --> 33:58.967
I could run a bath.

33:59.003 --> 34:00.800
I could light some candles.

34:00.838 --> 34:03.033
I think we're on the same page.

34:03.074 --> 34:04.564
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

34:12.116 --> 34:14.607
No more coffee for me, thanks.

34:14.652 --> 34:16.516
Could we have the check, please?

34:16.554 --> 34:19.545
It's on my father.
It's the least he can do.

34:19.590 --> 34:21.751
Antonia, your father's
on the phone.

34:21.793 --> 34:23.283
He'd like to speak to you.

34:23.327 --> 34:24.851
Thank you, Gerard.

34:24.896 --> 34:26.795
Excuse me while I go scold him.

34:26.831 --> 34:29.231
This was supposed
to be an evening with

34:29.266 --> 34:30.699
my two favorite men.

34:34.272 --> 34:36.137
I'll be right back.

34:45.983 --> 34:47.210
This seat taken?

34:47.251 --> 34:49.116
You're late.

34:49.152 --> 34:50.585
You didn't really think
I'd have dinner

34:50.621 --> 34:52.589
with the son of Jack McKay,
now, did you?

34:52.623 --> 34:54.523
Come on. I thought
you two were supposed

34:54.559 --> 34:55.650
to be such great friends.

34:55.693 --> 34:57.456
Let's make this
as brief as possible.

34:57.495 --> 34:58.757
What is it you want? Money?

34:58.796 --> 35:01.788
No. No, I want you
to give yourself up.

35:02.867 --> 35:04.892
Or die. It's your choice.

35:04.936 --> 35:08.929
You know, I thought
after my friend Tom E. Rose

35:09.006 --> 35:12.100
showed you the sights
of Palm Springs that,

35:12.143 --> 35:14.168
well, you knew what
you had coming.

35:14.212 --> 35:16.612
That's when I was afraid
of dying an unnatural death.

35:16.647 --> 35:17.909
Mm. And now you're not?

35:17.949 --> 35:19.576
And now I'm not.

35:19.617 --> 35:21.141
Because I have
a safe-deposit box,

35:21.185 --> 35:24.951
and in that box is enough
information to nail you.

35:24.989 --> 35:26.547
So if anything...

35:26.591 --> 35:29.560
anything happens to me,

35:29.594 --> 35:31.619
it's the gift
that keeps on giving.

35:35.032 --> 35:36.761
Stay away from my daughter.

35:36.801 --> 35:37.961
Or what?

35:38.035 --> 35:41.766
Or I'll have Ronnie here
just aim a little lower

35:41.806 --> 35:44.138
and wound you.

35:46.911 --> 35:49.971
Gentlemen, please,

35:50.081 --> 35:51.981
I mean,
coarse behavior like this?

35:52.083 --> 35:53.983
I am shocked.

35:54.085 --> 35:57.282
However, my opinion of you
is sufficiently low enough

35:57.321 --> 35:58.549
that I, too, came prepared.

36:06.731 --> 36:08.926
You wouldn't do anything
that stupid.

36:09.033 --> 36:10.864
Neither would you.

36:12.837 --> 36:14.361
So I'm gonna put my gun away.

36:14.405 --> 36:15.565
I'm gonna say good night...

36:16.874 --> 36:20.071
...and then I'm gonna
take Toni home.

36:20.111 --> 36:24.241
Actually, Antonia
is already on her way home.

36:24.282 --> 36:26.648
Yeah, well, that's too bad,

36:26.684 --> 36:28.345
because we were just getting
to the part

36:28.386 --> 36:31.082
where I tell her
how you killed my father.

36:34.759 --> 36:35.748
Get him out of here.

36:35.793 --> 36:36.760
No problem.

36:36.794 --> 36:37.761
Just ask...

36:37.795 --> 36:39.490
politely,

36:39.530 --> 36:41.327
and I'll leave.

36:43.634 --> 36:45.932
I'll leave...

36:45.970 --> 36:48.803
but I won't go away.

36:48.839 --> 36:51.774
I'm never going away

36:51.809 --> 36:53.936
until you're put away.

37:13.364 --> 37:15.332
Good morning, Donna.

37:15.366 --> 37:17.357
Oh, can we speak?

37:17.401 --> 37:19.335
The silence ended at daybreak.

37:19.370 --> 37:21.338
I kind of got used to the quiet.

37:21.372 --> 37:22.839
I even liked it.

37:22.873 --> 37:25.205
It's a nice respite from
the noise and confusion

37:25.243 --> 37:27.404
of everyday life.

37:27.445 --> 37:29.936
You know, I-I had
a dream last night.

37:30.014 --> 37:31.948
I dreamt that I left
my confusing life behind

37:32.049 --> 37:34.517
and took the oath of the church.

37:34.552 --> 37:37.612
I have the opposite dream
sometimes.

37:38.656 --> 37:39.953
I like it here.

37:39.991 --> 37:42.551
It's so simple and safe.

37:42.593 --> 37:44.288
I know if I lived your life,

37:44.328 --> 37:46.262
I wouldn't have
so much heartache.

37:46.297 --> 37:48.458
A boy?

37:48.499 --> 37:52.868
Yep, it's a recurring theme.

37:52.903 --> 37:56.168
I meet 'em,
I love 'em, they let me down.

37:56.207 --> 37:59.836
I notice how respectful
you are, Donna.

37:59.877 --> 38:01.868
The church must mean
a lot to you.

38:01.912 --> 38:04.813
It does.

38:04.849 --> 38:06.840
How'd you know
you wanted to be a nun?

38:06.884 --> 38:08.749
I had a calling.

38:08.786 --> 38:10.913
Do you think my dream
was a calling?

38:10.988 --> 38:12.012
If you had to ask,

38:12.056 --> 38:13.614
it wasn't.

38:13.658 --> 38:15.819
But you certainly don't have
to join an order

38:15.860 --> 38:17.088
to maintain your faith.

38:17.128 --> 38:19.494
Well, mine's been tested lately.

38:19.530 --> 38:20.929
It always will be.

38:20.998 --> 38:25.662
You have to remember what an
imperfect world we live in.

38:25.703 --> 38:26.931
With imperfect people.

38:26.971 --> 38:29.940
Which makes forgiveness
an important virtue.

38:30.007 --> 38:33.909
You know, Sister Alice,
you're good at this.

38:33.944 --> 38:36.708
That's why they pay me
the big bucks.

39:18.989 --> 39:20.923
I don't believe it.

39:21.025 --> 39:22.253
What?

39:24.428 --> 39:27.158
You passed the test.

39:27.198 --> 39:29.325
Well, I mean, last night
was pretty good.

39:29.367 --> 39:30.834
Oh, yeah, it was.

39:30.868 --> 39:32.529
But that's not what I mean.

39:32.570 --> 39:34.697
You made my bed.
That was my test.

39:34.739 --> 39:36.070
No one's ever passed before.

39:36.107 --> 39:37.131
Oh.

39:37.174 --> 39:40.302
Oh. Hey, hey, hey,
wait a minute.

39:40.344 --> 39:41.811
I just made this bed.

39:41.846 --> 39:43.279
Guess you'll have
to make it again.

39:43.314 --> 39:45.612
Mm. Oh, okay.

39:51.489 --> 39:54.049
I can't believe
it was just a broken water hose.

39:54.091 --> 39:56.082
Whatever.
It's fixed.

39:56.127 --> 39:58.493
Now we just have to find Donna.

39:58.529 --> 39:59.826
Good morning, sisters.

39:59.864 --> 40:01.593
So, I guess
we're talking now, huh?

40:01.632 --> 40:03.327
Silent time is over.

40:03.367 --> 40:05.426
But are we talking to me?

40:05.469 --> 40:07.960
Well, I'd like to make
an official peace offering.

40:08.005 --> 40:10.235
I've thought about it,
and what's done, is done.

40:10.274 --> 40:12.242
I think we should
put it behind us.

40:12.276 --> 40:13.470
All of us.

40:13.511 --> 40:15.069
If that's how you want it.

40:15.112 --> 40:16.670
Come on. Let's go say
bye to everybody.

40:16.714 --> 40:21.845
Uh, Donna, listen, um,

40:21.886 --> 40:23.285
I don't know what
you plan to say to Ray,

40:23.320 --> 40:25.754
but before you kiss and make up,

40:25.790 --> 40:27.348
make sure he's worth it.

40:27.391 --> 40:29.222
Are you talking
about Palm Springs?

40:29.260 --> 40:30.522
Yeah,

40:30.561 --> 40:33.587
and I can't forget what I saw
Ray do to you...

40:33.631 --> 40:35.690
and you shouldn't either.

40:54.452 --> 40:57.387
I didn't know
if I'd ever see you again.

40:57.421 --> 40:59.013
Well, maybe after today
you won't.

41:00.891 --> 41:02.222
My father told me

41:02.259 --> 41:03.783
some very upsetting things
about you, Dylan.

41:03.828 --> 41:07.195
Yeah? Like what?

41:07.231 --> 41:08.721
Like you used me.

41:10.167 --> 41:12.601
Like you have
some sort of vendetta.

41:12.636 --> 41:15.127
I can't lie to you.

41:15.172 --> 41:17.970
It started that way.

41:18.042 --> 41:20.567
It did...

41:20.611 --> 41:24.638
but that was before I saw you.

41:26.917 --> 41:28.612
My father is a good man.

41:28.652 --> 41:30.381
And if you knew him...

41:30.421 --> 41:34.448
I know that he had my father
blown to little pieces.

41:36.961 --> 41:39.930
He said that you were gonna try
to turn me against him.

41:39.964 --> 41:41.556
Toni,

41:41.599 --> 41:42.827
ask him.

41:42.867 --> 41:44.596
Ask anybody who knew
what was gonna happen

41:44.635 --> 41:47.160
when my Dad turned state's
evidence against him.

41:49.573 --> 41:50.801
You're wrong.

41:50.841 --> 41:53.935
My father could never
do anything like that.

41:59.550 --> 42:01.882
Then I guess there's nothing...

42:01.919 --> 42:03.887
left to say.

42:21.672 --> 42:23.537
What were you thinking?

42:23.574 --> 42:25.508
You're mounting
a big show in one week.

42:25.543 --> 42:27.101
How do you have time

42:27.144 --> 42:28.975
to paint a silly mural
for a nightclub?

42:29.046 --> 42:30.570
Claudia, back off.

42:30.614 --> 42:32.138
I'm ready for the show.

42:32.182 --> 42:33.649
I'm on top of it.

42:33.684 --> 42:34.708
I don't like it.

42:34.752 --> 42:37.346
And you sold yourself
way too cheap.

42:37.388 --> 42:39.288
How many times have I told you,

42:39.323 --> 42:42.690
artists don't negotiate
their own deals?

42:42.726 --> 42:45.160
And they should never negotiate
with old friends.

42:45.195 --> 42:47.163
Kelly...

42:47.197 --> 42:48.357
Hi, I'm Kelly Taylor.

42:48.399 --> 42:50.424
You must be Colin's art dealer.

42:50.467 --> 42:51.695
Claudia Van Eyck.

42:51.735 --> 42:53.430
What are you doing home so soon?

42:53.470 --> 42:54.937
You weren't due back
till tomorrow.

42:54.972 --> 42:56.997
It's a long story.

42:57.041 --> 42:58.508
Well, you can tell him
all about it.

42:58.542 --> 42:59.531
I'm on my way out.

42:59.577 --> 43:00.566
I'll see you at dinner.

43:00.611 --> 43:01.942
Nice to meet you, Kelly.

43:01.979 --> 43:03.276
You, too.

43:05.749 --> 43:07.580
Boy, am I glad to see you.

43:07.618 --> 43:09.279
Hmm... prove it.

43:15.459 --> 43:17.359
It's true, isn't it, Ray?

43:17.394 --> 43:18.554
Isn't it?!

43:18.596 --> 43:21.827
Okay. Okay, it's true.

43:21.865 --> 43:24.527
I slept with her once...

43:24.568 --> 43:25.933
and never again.

43:25.970 --> 43:27.335
And I knew it was a mistake.

43:27.371 --> 43:29.236
You are such a liar.

43:29.273 --> 43:30.797
Valerie told me

43:30.841 --> 43:32.240
all the details...
it was twice!

43:32.276 --> 43:34.267
That bitch.

43:34.311 --> 43:36.245
Yeah, well,
that bitch is my friend.

43:36.280 --> 43:37.611
And it's over.

43:37.648 --> 43:40.515
Don't do this, Donna, please!

43:40.551 --> 43:42.951
I'm begging you, do not do this.

43:42.987 --> 43:45.251
Or what?!
What are you gonna do?

43:45.289 --> 43:46.813
What're you gonna throw me
up against the wall

43:46.857 --> 43:48.188
like in Portland?

43:48.225 --> 43:50.523
Are you gonna push me down
the stairs like in Palm Springs?

43:50.561 --> 43:52.893
Or do you only hit me
when we're out of town?

43:53.931 --> 43:56.422
I love you, Donna.

43:56.467 --> 43:59.527
Please, you gotta
believe me, please.

44:01.038 --> 44:02.835
Forgive me.

44:02.873 --> 44:06.104
You know I have a lot
of forgiveness in my heart.

44:06.143 --> 44:09.078
I can even forgive Valerie,
but not you.

44:09.113 --> 44:10.637
Not for this!

44:20.624 --> 44:22.819
You're gonna regret this.

44:22.860 --> 44:26.455
What I regret is I didn't
do this a long time ago.

